A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Procurement Contracts and Memoranda of Understanding –
3 Reporting
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the reporting of certain procurement contracts and
5 memoranda of understanding entered into by certain public elementary and
6 secondary education systems in the State; and generally relating to procurement
7 contracts and memoranda of understanding entered into by education systems in the
8 State.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 2–307
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 2–307.
18 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
19 INDICATED.
20 (2) “COVERED ENTITY” MEANS:
21 (I) A COUNTY BOARD;
