5 (3) “PROCUREMENT CONTRACT” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
6 11–101 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
7 (B) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
8 THIS SECTION APPLIES TO:
9 (I) A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING ENTERED INTO BY A
10 COVERED ENTITY; AND
11 (II) A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT ENTERED INTO BY A COVERED
12 ENTITY.
13 (2) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT
14 OR MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING THAT INCLUDES INFORMATION THAT:
15 (I) MAY BE WITHHELD FROM DISCLOSURE BY LAW; OR
16 (II) IS PROHIBITED FROM DISCLOSURE BY LAW.
17 (C) (1) (I) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1 EACH YEAR, EACH COVERED
18 ENTITY SHALL REPORT TO THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT A LIST OF EACH
19 PROCUREMENT CONTRACT OR MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING ENTERED INTO
20 IN THE PRECEDING FISCAL YEAR BY THE COVERED ENTITY.
21 (II) A COVERED ENTITY THAT IS A COUNTY SUPERINTENDENT
22 OR A SCHOOL IN THE PUBLIC ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY EDUCATION SYSTEM
23 OF THE STATE MAY SATISFY THE REPORTING REQUIREMENT UNDER
24 SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH BY SUBMITTING THE REQUIRED
25 INFORMATION TO THE COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION BY A DATE DETERMINED BY
26 THE COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION.
27 (III) AS PART OF A REPORT MADE UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF
28 THIS PARAGRAPH, A COUNTY BOARD SHALL REPORT ANY INFORMATION RECEIVED
29 UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH.

